# Telnet (RFC 854, tcp:23) server initial option negotiation. On connect the server sends its opening
# IAC command run: "FF FB 01" (IAC WILL ECHO), "FF FB 03" (IAC WILL SUPPRESS-GO-AHEAD), "FF FD 1F"
# (IAC DO NAWS, window-size option 31), then the shell prompt data "/ # " (2f 20 23 20). The whole
# payload is kept verbatim (byte-perfect); the leading IAC run is parsed for display into
# {isNegotiation:true, commands:[WILL ECHO, WILL SGA, DO NAWS]}.
# source: REAL telnet negotiation captured from a busybox telnetd container
# (`docker run -p 2323:23 busybox telnetd -F -p 23 -l /bin/sh`) by reading the server's first bytes off
# a loopback socket — the exact application-layer payload was fffb01fffb03fffd1f2f202320. That genuine
# on-wire negotiation was then wrapped in an eth+ipv4+tcp frame by the netkitty encoder (src port 23,
# docker-bridge MACs/IPs 172.17.0.1→172.17.0.2) — the Telnet payload is the real server negotiation; the
# eth/ipv4/tcp envelope is synthesized. Verified [eth,ipv4,tcp,telnet] decode + byte-perfect round-trip.
